\title{Botnet Studies}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{Botnet architecture taxonomy, detection techniques, and defensive analysis. Covers C2 topologies, DGA analysis, fast-flux detection, P2P overlay mapping, blockchain C2, and ML-based traffic fingerprinting. Defensive research for understanding and countering distributed malicious infrastructure.}

\subtree{
\title{Botnet Studies: Defensive Architecture Analysis}
\p{\strong{Status}: Active \strong{Trit}: -1 (VALIDATOR вҖ” analyzes and constrains adversarial infrastructure) \strong{Context}: Defensive security research, CTF, authorized pentesting, academic study}

\subtree{
\title{Architecture Taxonomy}
\subtree{
\title{Topologies}
\pre{\startverb
| Topology | Resilience | Disruption Difficulty | Key Weakness |
|----------|-----------|----------------------|-------------|
| **Centralized C2** | Low | Low (sinkhole/seize) | Single point of failure |
| **Fast-flux** | Medium | Medium (DNS rotation) | TTL analysis reveals pattern |
| **P2P overlay** | High | High (graph fragmentation) | High-degree node removal |
| **Hybrid** (C2 + P2P fallback) | High | High | Must disrupt both layers |
| **Blockchain C2** | Very High | Very High (immutable state) | On-chain pattern analysis |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Modern Families (2025-2026)}
\pre{\startverb
| Family | Topology | Vector | Distinguishing Feature |
|--------|----------|--------|----------------------|
| Mirai variants (Gayfemboy, Jackskid, LZRD) | Centralized/Hybrid | IoT default creds, zero-days | Rust cross-compilation, 40K+ daily bots |
| Kimwolf | Centralized | Corporate/gov networks, Android TV | Dynamic C2 shifting |
| Aisuru | Centralized | IoT mass compromise | Record DDoS volume, real-time load shifting |
| Tsundere | Blockchain C2 | Game installer masquerade | Ethereum smart contract stores C2 URLs |
| Badbox 2.0 | Centralized | Pre-installed Android malware | 10M devices as residential proxies |
| Emotet | Centralized | Phishing вҶ’ loader chain | Periodic resurrection post-takedown |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Blockchain C2 (Emerging Threat)}
\pre{\startverb
Operator вҶ’ 0 ETH tx вҶ’ Smart Contract (state update: new C2 URL)
                              вҶ“
Bot вҶ’ public RPC вҶ’ read contract state вҶ’ connect to new C2
\stopverb}

\p{Immutable. Cannot be seized. Traditional sinkholing fails. Counter: on-chain pattern analysis, RPC endpoint monitoring, contract interaction fingerprinting.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Detection Techniques}
\subtree{
\title{DGA Analysis}
\p{Domain Generation Algorithms produce pseudo-random domains (thousands/day). Only botmaster knows the seed вҶ’ can pre-register the right ones.}

\pre{\startverb
| Method | Approach | Strengths |
|--------|----------|-----------|
| Feature engineering | Entropy, n-gram freq, consonant/vowel ratio вҶ’ RF/XGBoost | Interpretable, fast |
| BiLSTM + CNN + Attention | Character-level sequence classification | No manual features |
| LLM fine-tuning (SFT) | GPT on domain character sequences | Low false positive rate |
| LLM in-context learning | Few-shot DGA family adaptation | Zero retrain for new families |
| GPT embedding + CNN | Dense vector representation вҶ’ CNN classifier | Combines semantic + structural |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Zig SIMD opportunity}: Domain entropy computation across batch of 10K domains. Shannon entropy of character distribution вҖ” embarrassingly parallel, pure arithmetic.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Fast-Flux Detection}
\pre{\startverb
| Signal | Normal DNS | Fast-Flux |
|--------|-----------|-----------|
| TTL | 3600-86400s | 0-300s |
| A-record count per query | 1-4 | 10-100+ over time |
| ASN diversity | 1-2 | 10-50+ |
| Geographic spread | 1-2 countries | 20+ countries |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Traffic Fingerprinting}
\ul{
\li{Flow-level: packet size distribution, inter-arrival times}
\li{Payload: encrypted channel fingerprints (JA3/JA4 TLS fingerprinting)}
\li{Behavioral: connection patterns, beacon intervals, sleep jitter}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Honeypot/Honeynet}
\ul{
\li{Adaptive deception systems (federated honeypots)}
\li{IoT-specific honeynets (Cowrie SSH, Dionaea SMB, Conpot SCADA)}
\li{ML classifiers on honeypot log features}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Analysis Tools}
\pre{\startverb
| Tool | Role | Integration |
|------|------|-------------|
| **CAPE Sandbox** | Dynamic malware analysis (successor to Cuckoo) | Auto-unpack, config extract |
| **MISP** | Threat intelligence sharing (IOCs) | API for automated IOC ingestion |
| **TheHive** | Incident response case management | Integrates MISP + Cortex |
| **Cortex** | Observable analysis engine | 100+ analyzers (geoloc, reputation, sandbox) |
| **Zeek** | Network metadata extraction | Passive DNS, protocol logs, DGA detection |
| **Suricata** | IDS/IPS deep packet inspection | Real-time botnet traffic signatures |
| **Wazuh** | SIEM/EDR | Host-based detection, log correlation |
\stopverb}

\p{SOC stack: Wazuh + TheHive + Cortex + MISP + Zeek/Suricata + CAPE}
}

\subtree{
\title{Game-Theoretic Framing}
\subtree{
\title{Botnet as Open Game}
\pre{\startverb
     Attacker                    Defender
   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ              в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
   в”Ӯ Infect   в”Ӯв”Җв”Җpayoffsв”Җв”ҖвҶ’  в”Ӯ Detect       в”Ӯ
   в”Ӯ C2 Comm  в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ Sinkhole     в”Ӯ
   в”Ӯ Exfil    в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ Patch        в”Ӯ
   в”Ӯ Monetize в”Ӯ              в”Ӯ Takedown     в”Ӯ
   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ              в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ

Sequential composition: Infect ; C2 ; Payload ; Exfil
Monoidal product: Phishing вҠ— IoT_exploit вҠ— Supply_chain

Bayesian open games: incomplete information (which hosts compromised?)
Coplay function: defender backward analysis of attacker incentives
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Equilibrium Models}
\pre{\startverb
| Model | Structure | Application |
|-------|-----------|-------------|
| **Stackelberg** | Leader-follower (defender commits first) | Resource allocation across network segments |
| **FlipIt** | Stealth control-flipping | MTD timing decisions |
| **Colonel Blotto** | Simultaneous multi-target allocation | Monitoring budget distribution |
| **SIS epidemic** | Susceptible-Infected-Susceptible | Propagation dynamics + intervention |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Nashator Integration}
\pre{\startverb
;; Botnet attack-defense as open game via Nashator
(define botnet-game
  (DSL.game "botnet_attack_defense"
    (list (DSL.player "Attacker" +1 4)   ; 4 strategies: infect/c2/exfil/persist
          (DSL.player "Defender" -1 4))   ; 4 strategies: detect/sinkhole/patch/takedown
    ;; Payoff matrix from empirical data
    botnet-payoffs))

;; Compose with capability defense game
(define defended-game
  (DSL.seq botnet-game capability-defense-game))
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Capability-Based Defense (OCapN)}
\subtree{
\title{Why Botnets Succeed}
\pre{\startverb
Ambient authority: process runs as user вҶ’ inherits ALL user permissions
Compromise one process вҶ’ lateral movement to everything user can access
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Why Capabilities Prevent This}
\pre{\startverb
Structural authority: process holds ONLY explicitly granted references
Compromise one process вҶ’ attacker gets only those specific capabilities
No network scan cap вҶ’ cannot discover other hosts
No outbound socket cap вҶ’ cannot phone home to C2
No firmware write cap вҶ’ cannot persist
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Goblins Actor as Hardened Endpoint}
\pre{\startverb
(define (^iot-service bcom http-port-cap log-cap)
  "IoT service with ONLY the capabilities it needs.
   Cannot scan network. Cannot write firmware. Cannot phone home."
  (methods
    [(handle-request req)
     ;; Can only use http-port-cap and log-cap
     ;; Even if compromised, attacker gains nothing beyond these
     ($ log-cap write (format "request: ~a" req))
     (serve-response http-port-cap req)]))
\stopverb}
}
}

